702738f-a.text:
(1)
East 38th Street, north from Ave. U, showing the Elisha Kimball house, which, in 1919 was circled by a porch, and did not have the observation atop. It, probably, was added when the "Sheepshead Bay Race
Track" came into use.
August 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, looking south.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(3)
The same, remodeled, showing also, partially, homes facing Ave. U.
February 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
